WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.720
When AI steals your work, the legal power to force its deletion is called algorithmic

2
00:00:05.720 --> 00:00:07.200
discouragement.

3
00:00:07.200 --> 00:00:12.120
But while AI moves at lightning speed, the law lags far behind.

4
00:00:12.120 --> 00:00:17.480
Take a Canadian illustrator who found dozens of AI images copying his exact artwork without

5
00:00:17.480 --> 00:00:19.040
his consent.

6
00:00:19.040 --> 00:00:24.280
It begins with web-screeping, automated tools extract massive volumes of internet images

7
00:00:24.280 --> 00:00:26.840
to build a prepared data set.

8
00:00:26.840 --> 00:00:32.240
This data set teaches a system's statistical patterns so it can produce derivative works,

9
00:00:32.240 --> 00:00:36.800
building what's known as a generative model, entirely without the original creator's

10
00:00:36.800 --> 00:00:38.120
awareness.

11
00:00:38.120 --> 00:00:43.840
Canada's proposed AI and data act aims to regulate this pipeline, but it defers specific

12
00:00:43.840 --> 00:00:49.840
rules to future regulations and open-ended approach critics call a blank check.

13
00:00:49.840 --> 00:00:55.560
Because the technology operates now while rules are delayed, the law lacks proactive teeth.

14
00:00:55.560 --> 00:01:00.200
It has no mechanism to investigate companies currently suspected of intellectual property

15
00:01:00.200 --> 00:01:01.200
theft.

16
00:01:01.200 --> 00:01:06.800
Crucially, it omits the power to mandate the destruction of models built on stolen data.

17
00:01:06.800 --> 00:01:10.680
That specific deletion power is algorithmic discouragement.

18
00:01:10.680 --> 00:01:15.800
Without it, the legislation can't undo the economic harm, already permanently embedded

19
00:01:15.800 --> 00:01:17.480
in these systems.

20
00:01:17.480 --> 00:01:21.800
And what about that Canadian illustrator stolen artwork from the beginning?

21
00:01:21.800 --> 00:01:26.400
While the law can order data set destruction, his exact style remains trapped inside the

22
00:01:26.400 --> 00:01:26.880
machine.
